# Event geo dedup

## Rule

Merge registry `event_id` values only when **normalized name + geo_key** match.

- Same name, **different city/country** → two geo-events (do not merge).
- Same name, **same geo** → merge candidate (duplicate WSDC ids).
- **Metro clusters** (e.g. Boston + Framingham, MA) count as one geo for merge.

## Keep separate (hardcoded)

| event_ids | Reason |
|-----------|--------|
| 75, 152 | Worlds UCWDC — Dallas vs Orlando |
| 191, 230 | Sunny Side Dance Camp — Crimea vs Spain |
| 83, 204 | Spring Swing — Detroit vs Stockholm |

## Implementation

- `transform/geography/geo_event.py` — `geo_key`, `METRO_CLUSTERS`, `classify_event_id_pair`
- `transform/knowledge/event_aliases.py` — `MERGE_EVENT_ID_MAP` (source → canonical)
- `scripts/merge_event_ids.py` — always `--dry-run` first; verify geo gate
- `scripts/audit_event_splits.py` — classify split pairs before merge

## Do not

- Merge across different `geo_key` without explicit user approval
- Rename `core.events.name` for rebrand-only changes (breaks history join)
- Delete merged `event_id` rows — remap `core.results.event_id` only
